1 than fifty percent (50%) of its annual budget on instructional
2 expenditures.
3 B. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
4 its annual budget on instructional expenditures, it shall increase
5 its instructional expenditures by no less than two percent (2%) each
6 year until the amount spent on instructional expenditures reaches
7 fifty percent (50%) of its annual budget.
8 C. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
9 its annual budget on instructional expenditures and does not
10 increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this section,
11 the school district shall receive a written warning notice from the
12 State Department of Education. The notice shall also be posted on
13 the website of the school district.
14 D. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
15 its annual budget on instructional expenditures and does not
16 increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this section
17 for four (4) consecutive years after receiving the notice provided
18 in subsection C of this section, the school district shall increase
19 compensation for all teachers in the school district by two percent
20 (2%) for each year in that period in which the school district did
21 not increase instructional expenditures by a minimum of two percent
22 (2%). The pay increase required pursuant to this subsection shall
23 be permanent.
24 E. As used in this section:
